New Records: Mitchell Santner became the first New Zealand spinner to take a five-wicket haul at a Cricket World Cup.
Key Match Events: Mitchell Santner took five wickets for 59 runs.
Santner made a quickfire unbeaten 36 off 17 balls.
Netherlands were bowled out for 223 in 46.3 overs.
Colin Ackermann made a battling half-century with 69 runs.
Trent Boult took a superb juggling catch to dismiss Bas de Leede.
Miscellaneous Highlights: New Zealand didn’t feel the absence of captain Kane Williamson.
Netherlands lost their second consecutive match after losing to Pakistan.
New Zealand avenged their 2019 World Cup final defeat by beating England in their previous match.
